################################## HAVING BY ##################################

Filter Aggregated Data It means Filters Data After Aggregation
Note: So We can only use Having only after Group By

SELECT CUSTOMER_ID,
        SUM(BALANCE)
FROM TABLE
GROUP BY CUSTOMER_ID
HAVING CONDITION MEANS SUM(BALANCE) > 3000

If we want to filter data before aggregation we use WHERE 
If we want to filter data after  aggregation we use HAVINNG (CONDITION)


################################## DISTINCT ##################################

It removes duplicates (Repeated values) means each value appears only once.
Don't use DISTINCT unless it's necessary; It can slow down your query. Use for only duplication in your data

